And someday...

272
00:39:24,349 --> 00:39:27,124
if you find your dream and become an actress,

273
00:39:27,124 --> 00:39:31,610
I hope we meet again on the same project.

274
00:39:43,301 --> 00:39:45,418
- Yeah?
- Sounds like...

275
00:39:45,418 --> 00:39:47,744
there's a copy of Chu Sang Ah's recording.

276
00:39:47,744 --> 00:39:50,497
Where are you right now?

277
00:39:50,497 --> 00:39:54,168
I don't do this for money.

278
00:39:54,168 --> 00:39:57,814
What drives me is

279
00:39:57,814 --> 00:39:59,618
a sense of duty.

280
00:39:59,618 --> 00:40:02,838
And what kind of duty is that?

281
00:40:04,785 --> 00:40:07,708
People living in

282
00:40:07,708 --> 00:40:12,716
this twisted, hellish world need somewhere

283
00:40:12,716 --> 00:40:16,127
to vent their anger.

284
00:40:16,127 --> 00:40:18,773
A witch hunt.

285
00:40:19,381 --> 00:40:22,624
I just want to find the real witches
hiding among us,

286
00:40:22,624 --> 00:40:25,698
put them on the stake,

287
00:40:25,698 --> 00:40:28,998
expose what they really are,

288
00:40:29,792 --> 00:40:33,038
and deliver justice.

289
00:40:34,957 --> 00:40:37,714
[Director Lee Yang Mi]

290
00:40:40,214 --> 00:40:41,252
Hello.

291
00:40:41,252 --> 00:40:44,483
So what's our next move?

292
00:40:44,483 --> 00:40:45,913
We'll reach out to Park Jae Sang

293
00:40:45,913 --> 00:40:48,533
and release the copy of the recording
by tomorrow.

294
00:40:48,533 --> 00:40:49,886
Okay.

295
00:40:49,886 --> 00:40:51,833
Bang Tae Seop and Chu Sang Ah
going up in flames.

296
00:40:51,833 --> 00:40:53,414
What a sight.

297
00:40:53,414 --> 00:40:56,367
Make sure it turns into a full-blown wildfire.
Wrap it up cleanly.

298
00:40:56,367 --> 00:40:58,780
Understood.

299
00:41:00,765 --> 00:41:02,179
How's the chairman today?

300
00:41:02,179 --> 00:41:06,778
Blood sugar is 252,
and his blood pressure is 170.

301
00:41:06,778 --> 00:41:08,182
Oh, come on.

302
00:41:08,182 --> 00:41:10,031
That old man needs to stay alive
a few more months

303
00:41:10,031 --> 00:41:12,120
if we're going to get those papers sorted.

304
00:41:12,120 --> 00:41:14,363
Gosh.

305
00:41:15,722 --> 00:41:18,635
Oh, there she is, my princess!

306
00:41:18,635 --> 00:41:21,876
Mom, my stress levels
are through the roof today.

307
00:41:21,876 --> 00:41:24,300
Do I really have to put on a show
in front of Dad?

308
00:41:24,300 --> 00:41:27,006
Oh, I see.

309
00:41:27,006 --> 00:41:31,009
But you know your dad loves you
more than anything.

310
00:41:31,009 --> 00:41:36,830
If you celebrate his birthday,
he'll be so happy.

311
00:41:36,830 --> 00:41:39,890
Fine. I guess I have no choice.

312
00:41:41,491 --> 00:41:44,684
So, what are we wearing today?

313
00:41:45,717 --> 00:41:48,579
Since it's the chairman's birthday,
a very special occasion,

314
00:41:48,579 --> 00:41:50,738
I prepared looks tailored
to each of your personal colors,

315
00:41:50,738 --> 00:41:53,178
taking hair and makeup into account.

316
00:41:53,178 --> 00:41:55,901
His blood pressure is 170 today.

317
00:41:55,901 --> 00:41:57,370
Forget personal colors.

318
00:41:57,370 --> 00:41:59,201
Do you really think
something this bold is appropriate?

319
00:41:59,201 --> 00:42:01,874
Please, think about the goal here.

320
00:42:01,874 --> 00:42:04,582
Exactly.

321
00:42:04,582 --> 00:42:08,008
Right. I'll prepare new options right away.

322
00:42:08,774 --> 00:42:11,887
Next. Director Cha.

323
00:42:16,292 --> 00:42:19,102
For Hee Jin today, I pulled some references of

324
00:42:19,102 --> 00:42:21,769
those trendy Hollywood star daughters

325
00:42:21,769 --> 00:42:25,656
who've been winning people over lately,
aligned with our strategy.

326
00:42:25,656 --> 00:42:28,568
What do you think of this cute concept?

327
00:42:28,568 --> 00:42:29,956
Oh no,

328
00:42:29,956 --> 00:42:32,027
not cute today.

329
00:42:32,027 --> 00:42:34,753
Go with something that triggers
a protective instinct.

330
00:42:34,753 --> 00:42:37,526
Yes, ma'am.

331
00:42:40,293 --> 00:42:41,530
Hee Jin,

332
00:42:41,530 --> 00:42:43,891
try what you practiced earlier.

333
00:42:43,891 --> 00:42:46,157
Okay.

334
00:42:47,544 --> 00:42:50,981
♪ I ran to you with the biggest smile ♪

335
00:42:50,981 --> 00:42:54,655
♪ So happy to see you, Dad ♪

336
00:42:54,655 --> 00:43:03,022
♪ But somehow you look a little down today ♪

337
00:43:03,022 --> 00:43:07,019
♪ Did something happen ♪

338
00:43:07,019 --> 00:43:10,856
♪ Is something weighing on your mind ♪

339
00:43:10,856 --> 00:43:18,397
♪ Did things not go your way today ♪

340
00:43:18,397 --> 00:43:21,981
♪ Dad, stay strong ♪

341
00:43:21,981 --> 00:43:26,365
♪ I'm right here with you ♪

342
00:43:26,365 --> 00:43:29,629
♪ Dad, stay strong ♪

343
00:43:29,629 --> 00:43:33,926
♪ I'm right here with you ♪

344
00:43:33,926 --> 00:43:37,386
I love you, Dad.

345
00:43:39,571 --> 00:43:41,223
Oh, my princess.

346
00:43:41,223 --> 00:43:42,516
That was wonderful.

347
00:43:42,516 --> 00:43:47,399
Oh, my girl is the reason I keep going.

348
00:43:52,707 --> 00:43:54,820
Darn it.

349
00:43:58,144 --> 00:44:01,401
Dragging in a five-year-old daughter
in a power play between the adults?

350
00:44:01,401 --> 00:44:03,848
That's just low.

351
00:44:03,848 --> 00:44:09,594
Maybe you should've treated
your wife a little better.

352
00:44:09,594 --> 00:44:10,951
By the way,

353
00:44:10,951 --> 00:44:14,178
you can't drop Bang Tae Seop, can you?

354
00:44:14,178 --> 00:44:16,658
Yeah.

355
00:44:16,658 --> 00:44:19,356
That's actually what I came to talk about.

356
00:44:19,356 --> 00:44:22,261
What is it?

357
00:44:22,261 --> 00:44:24,481
The Oh Kwang Jae case...

358
00:44:24,481 --> 00:44:27,708
That was you, wasn't it?

359
00:44:27,708 --> 00:44:29,595
Me?

360
00:44:29,595 --> 00:44:32,491
After Bang Tae Seop messed up
the Nam Hye Hoon deal,

361
00:44:32,491 --> 00:44:35,281
you got bitter and stirred this up
to screw them...

362
00:44:35,281 --> 00:44:37,905
and me too,

363
00:44:37,905 --> 00:44:41,367
didn't you?

364
00:44:41,367 --> 00:44:43,464
Stop making things up
and worry about your own mess.

365
00:44:43,464 --> 00:44:45,153
Just tell me the truth!

366
00:44:45,153 --> 00:44:46,603
What is wrong with you?

367
00:44:46,603 --> 00:44:50,836
Of all things, why would you blow that up?

368
00:44:50,836 --> 00:44:55,856
You came in late as the second wife,
so you don't know my father's history, but...

369
00:44:56,823 --> 00:44:59,060
If you mess with the Oh Kwang Jae case,

370
00:44:59,060 --> 00:45:02,681
this whole family blows up!

371
00:45:02,681 --> 00:45:05,828
What are you talking about?

372
00:45:09,275 --> 00:45:14,105
My father was tied up in that case too.

373
00:45:14,714 --> 00:45:16,741
Why would the chairman be involved?

374
00:45:16,741 --> 00:45:18,894
Oh Kwang Jae got screwed over

375
00:45:18,894 --> 00:45:22,868
by my father on that China deal, held a grudge,

376
00:45:22,868 --> 00:45:24,744
and tried to blackmail him with it.

377
00:45:24,744 --> 00:45:27,235
That's how it all went down.

378
00:45:27,235 --> 00:45:29,440
What?

379
00:45:29,440 --> 00:45:30,791
Then the one who killed him...

380
00:45:30,791 --> 00:45:35,318
Bang Tae Seop's probably the only one
who knows for sure,

381
00:45:35,318 --> 00:45:38,811
but doesn't it look like my father?

382
00:45:42,741 --> 00:45:45,234
You're adorable.

383
00:45:47,098 --> 00:45:50,238
What an idiot.

384
00:46:21,592 --> 00:46:24,923
[Penalty for Contract Cancellation]
I'm so sorry.

385
00:46:26,141 --> 00:46:30,394
I'll take care of it. I'm sorry.

386
00:46:31,435 --> 00:46:32,645
[Guess she's been acting her whole life]

387
00:46:32,645 --> 00:46:35,845
Once I added up the penalties

388
00:46:35,845 --> 00:46:37,803
from the ads and the film,

389
00:46:37,803 --> 00:46:39,292
it's just brutal.

390
00:46:39,292 --> 00:46:41,268
I went around asking them

391
00:46:41,268 --> 00:46:45,157
to give us a little more time,

392
00:46:45,157 --> 00:46:47,368
but none of it's working.

393
00:46:47,368 --> 00:46:50,819
You're looking for Park Jae Sang, right?

394
00:46:50,819 --> 00:46:53,637
Yeah. I hired a private investigator,

395
00:46:53,637 --> 00:46:55,840
and we're searching everywhere, but...

396
00:46:55,840 --> 00:46:59,085
They say if he's in Seoam
without any phone records,

397
00:46:59,085 --> 00:47:00,256
he's basically impossible to track.

398
00:47:00,256 --> 00:47:03,804
Could take at least a month.

399
00:47:04,453 --> 00:47:07,926
Even if Choi Ji Ho won't meet,

400
00:47:07,926 --> 00:47:10,077
we have to stop the second broadcast,
no matter what.

401
00:47:10,077 --> 00:47:12,750
I really want that too.

402
00:47:12,750 --> 00:47:18,136
But he's being so hardline about it.

403
00:47:19,705 --> 00:47:22,570
What are you going to do?

404
00:47:22,570 --> 00:47:26,597
I'll find Park Jae Sang.

405
00:47:26,597 --> 00:47:28,374
Sang Ah.

406
00:47:28,374 --> 00:47:30,943
Sang Ah.

407
00:48:02,104 --> 00:48:04,637
Is this the place?

408
00:48:25,061 --> 00:48:28,256
- Hey, ma'am!
- Oh, sorry.

409
00:48:28,256 --> 00:48:30,645
I told you not to do this here!

410
00:48:30,645 --> 00:48:32,435
I'm sorry.

411
00:48:32,435 --> 00:48:34,760
You're making a mess of the whole neighborhood.

412
00:48:34,760 --> 00:48:38,326
How many times do I have to tell you?

413
00:48:38,326 --> 00:48:40,837
I'm sick of saying it.

414
00:48:40,837 --> 00:48:44,418
Customers are coming. Clean this up, now!

415
00:48:44,418 --> 00:48:45,805
I will.

416
00:48:45,805 --> 00:48:49,673
What is wrong with her? This is so stressful.

417
00:49:03,057 --> 00:49:05,405
You don't look well.

418
00:49:05,405 --> 00:49:09,218
Could this be your last birthday?

419
00:49:27,988 --> 00:49:30,761
You think

420
00:49:30,761 --> 00:49:34,287
I'm that easy to take down?

421
00:49:34,287 --> 00:49:37,420
I'm not dying.

422
00:49:47,484 --> 00:49:49,642
I brought something

423
00:49:49,642 --> 00:49:53,308
I've been sitting on for a long time.

424
00:49:54,675 --> 00:49:59,815
Proof that you're the real killer
in the Oh Kwang Jae case.

425
00:50:04,835 --> 00:50:06,099
[Case Records in 2018]

426
00:50:06,099 --> 00:50:08,290
[Criminal Case Records]

427
00:50:10,413 --> 00:50:13,087
Not bad.

428
00:50:14,265 --> 00:50:17,104
You've slipped through tighter nets before,

429
00:50:17,104 --> 00:50:20,335
but this won't be so easy.

430
00:50:20,335 --> 00:50:25,248
So you're going down with me?
As the prosecutor who twisted the truth?

431
00:50:29,377 --> 00:50:32,231
Go ahead. Do it.

432
00:50:36,871 --> 00:50:39,524
Fine by me.

433
00:50:40,645 --> 00:50:43,957
I've got nothing left to lose anyway.

434
00:50:53,781 --> 00:50:55,372
Where's the chairman right now?

435
00:50:55,372 --> 00:50:56,562
He's over there.

436
00:50:56,562 --> 00:50:59,362
- Is he resting?
- Yes.

437
00:51:10,391 --> 00:51:13,688
Even if you get arrested,
you'll just post bail,

438
00:51:13,688 --> 00:51:16,598
given your age and condition...

439
00:51:16,598 --> 00:51:19,744
- What is he talking about?
- But the reputation WR built...

440
00:51:19,744 --> 00:51:23,524
It'll be your legacy that gets stained.

441
00:51:24,218 --> 00:51:28,444
And your daughter, Hee Jin...

442
00:51:30,208 --> 00:51:34,348
she'll spend her life known as
a killer's daughter.

443
00:51:40,587 --> 00:51:43,926
What do you want?

444
00:51:50,018 --> 00:51:53,898
Those stories about me and Sang Ah...

445
00:51:56,039 --> 00:51:58,652
They all started

446
00:51:59,406 --> 00:52:03,772
with your wife, Director Lee Yang Mi.

447
00:52:09,643 --> 00:52:13,283
Please handle it quickly at your level.

448
00:52:13,283 --> 00:52:18,409
Then I'll destroy these documents
and bury it for good.

449
00:52:18,409 --> 00:52:22,276
Call me when it's done. I'll be waiting.

450
00:52:36,590 --> 00:52:37,968
Oh gosh.

451
00:52:37,968 --> 00:52:41,266
Oh my, Chairman!

452
00:52:41,956 --> 00:52:45,791
Get it together, please!

453
00:52:45,791 --> 00:52:49,070
Useless...

454
00:52:54,735 --> 00:52:57,366
Talk to you later.

455
00:52:59,085 --> 00:53:01,772
Prosecutor Bang!

456
00:53:19,612 --> 00:53:22,138
What is that smell?

457
00:53:24,725 --> 00:53:27,231
Shit.

458
00:53:37,570 --> 00:53:40,549
This is an emergency.

459
00:53:43,148 --> 00:53:47,694
All personnel, move to the annex immediately.

460
00:54:04,176 --> 00:54:06,649
Darn it.

461
00:54:31,603 --> 00:54:32,624
Director.

462
00:54:32,624 --> 00:54:37,630
Should we call 119?

463
00:54:37,630 --> 00:54:39,477
Hey.

464
00:54:39,477 --> 00:54:41,341
Are you insane?

465
00:54:41,341 --> 00:54:43,624
You want to blast it everywhere

466
00:54:43,624 --> 00:54:48,443
that the WR owner is dying?

467
00:54:49,509 --> 00:54:52,493
Do you even think?

468
00:54:52,493 --> 00:54:55,553
I'm sorry.

469
00:55:45,494 --> 00:55:48,141
Chairman.

470
00:55:56,186 --> 00:56:00,550
You know I've done everything I could for you,

471
00:56:00,550 --> 00:56:02,863
right?

472
00:56:04,883 --> 00:56:08,210
When you go...

473
00:56:17,230 --> 00:56:21,977
Make sure Hee Jin's shares are
clearly secured in your will.

474
00:56:21,977 --> 00:56:24,270
Yeah?

475
00:56:30,258 --> 00:56:32,732
You...

476
00:56:35,577 --> 00:56:37,897
Yes?

477
00:56:55,738 --> 00:56:59,286
Whatever you're pulling,

478
00:56:59,286 --> 00:57:02,418
shut it down.

479
00:57:20,649 --> 00:57:23,068
Yeah,

480
00:57:24,194 --> 00:57:28,238
I had no idea, you'd been working yourself

481
00:57:28,238 --> 00:57:31,621
to the bone like that.

482
00:57:39,537 --> 00:57:44,050
Director, is there anything I can help with?

483
00:57:45,216 --> 00:57:48,109
I'm sorry.

484
00:57:51,463 --> 00:57:53,979
We should bury the recording.

485
00:57:53,979 --> 00:57:56,569
Yeah.

486
00:57:56,569 --> 00:58:00,289
We're killing this project here.

487
00:58:00,289 --> 00:58:03,533
Pull everything tied to
Park Jae Sang and Oh Kwang Jae.

488
00:58:03,533 --> 00:58:05,796
And shelve the recording release.

489
00:58:05,796 --> 00:58:06,821
Understood.

490
00:58:06,821 --> 00:58:10,574
With the chairman involved,
it's too risky to keep pushing.

491
00:58:10,574 --> 00:58:15,180
I'll reach out to Park Jae Sang
and put the project on hold.

492
00:58:15,180 --> 00:58:16,974
And

493
00:58:16,974 --> 00:58:19,971
bring me a Plan B.

494
00:58:19,971 --> 00:58:22,437
Got it.

495
00:58:26,303 --> 00:58:28,663
Damn it.

496
00:58:32,058 --> 00:58:34,725
Mr. Park,

497
00:58:34,725 --> 00:58:37,775
we're calling off the recording release.

498
00:58:37,775 --> 00:58:40,055
What?

499
00:58:40,742 --> 00:58:44,118
Are you kidding me right now?

500
00:58:44,118 --> 00:58:47,815
Choi Ji Ho's not meeting Park Jae Sang today.

501
00:58:47,815 --> 00:58:49,899
Looks like Lee Yang Mi pulled the plug.

502
00:58:49,899 --> 00:58:52,622
They just shut down the recording,

503
00:58:52,622 --> 00:58:55,302
and Park Jae Sang sounds pissed.

504
00:58:55,302 --> 00:58:58,081
I'll stay on him.

505
00:59:06,064 --> 00:59:08,054
Why are you doing this now?

506
00:59:08,054 --> 00:59:11,111
It's complicated. Let's meet later and...

507
00:59:11,111 --> 00:59:14,071
"Later?" When the hell is later?

508
00:59:14,071 --> 00:59:17,844
You're the one who dragged me into this.

509
00:59:20,059 --> 00:59:23,099
If you want out, you get out.

510
00:59:23,966 --> 00:59:25,834
I'm not letting Chu Sang Ah go.

511
00:59:25,834 --> 00:59:28,340
Hey, Mr. Park...

512
00:59:29,626 --> 00:59:31,916
Don't do anything rash...

513
00:59:31,916 --> 00:59:33,433
Hey!

514
00:59:33,433 --> 00:59:35,799
Damn it.

515
00:59:36,572 --> 00:59:38,796
The number you have dialed is not available.

516
00:59:38,796 --> 00:59:42,389
Why isn't he picking up?

517
00:59:45,539 --> 00:59:47,992
Leech.

518
00:59:49,831 --> 00:59:52,378
What the...

519
00:59:58,146 --> 00:59:59,485
Oh my,

520
00:59:59,485 --> 01:00:01,820
such a sweet girl helping with this...

521
01:00:01,820 --> 01:00:04,123
It's nothing.

522
01:00:17,145 --> 01:00:19,251
Well...

523
01:00:20,645 --> 01:00:22,855
You don't recognize me?

524
01:00:22,855 --> 01:00:24,362
I feel like

525
01:00:24,362 --> 01:00:27,929
I've seen you somewhere.

526
01:00:27,929 --> 01:00:31,782
About Jae Sang... from before...

527
01:00:36,865 --> 01:00:38,982
Then you're...

528
01:00:38,982 --> 01:00:42,047
Chu Sang Ah?

529
01:00:42,047 --> 01:00:44,554
I'm sorry.

530
01:00:45,166 --> 01:00:48,766
I was just overwhelmed back then.

531
01:00:50,454 --> 01:00:54,533
I never thought it would actually happen.

532
01:00:56,072 --> 01:00:58,002
Just once...

533
01:00:58,002 --> 01:01:01,209
Just forgive me, please.

534
01:01:02,025 --> 01:01:04,432
- I'm sorry.
- Don't do this.

535
01:01:04,432 --> 01:01:07,424
Please forgive me.

536
01:01:07,424 --> 01:01:09,202
I'm sorry.

537
01:01:09,202 --> 01:01:13,451
I'm so sorry, ma'am. I didn't know back then.

538
01:01:13,451 --> 01:01:17,579
I didn't know you can't just walk away
after ruining someone's life.

539
01:01:17,579 --> 01:01:19,022
I'm sorry.

540
01:01:19,022 --> 01:01:22,450
Please don't do this.

541
01:01:22,450 --> 01:01:25,372
Please forgive me.

542
01:01:26,086 --> 01:01:29,112
I'm so sorry.

543
01:01:29,749 --> 01:01:32,547
- I'm sorry.
- Sang Ah.

544
01:01:49,028 --> 01:01:51,801
It's been a while,

545
01:01:55,440 --> 01:01:57,825
Park Jae Sang.

546
01:02:43,191 --> 01:02:46,142
You were with Sang Ah last night, weren't you?

547
01:02:46,142 --> 01:02:49,167
Why are you so on edge?

548
01:02:49,167 --> 01:02:51,623
Let's end this.

549
01:02:51,623 --> 01:02:53,352
I can't end it like this.

550
01:02:53,352 --> 01:02:54,821
I'm going to expose everything.

551
01:02:54,821 --> 01:02:56,062
You know,

552
01:02:56,062 --> 01:02:58,575
if Chu Sang Ah goes down,
so does Prosecutor Bang.

553
01:02:58,575 --> 01:03:01,032
I'll stop him,
even if I have to kill the bastard.

554
01:03:01,032 --> 01:03:04,219
I'll take point on the tentpole.

555
01:03:04,219 --> 01:03:07,212
Make it bold

556
01:03:07,212 --> 01:03:10,012
and hit hard.
